Fresh progress has been made in work related to Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan over the past five years, according to a government work report submitted to the national legislature for deliberation on Sunday. The central government has effectively exercised full jurisdiction over the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) in accordance with the Constitution and the Basic Law, the report said. The Law of the People's Republic of China on Safeguarding National Security in the HKSAR has been formulated and put into effect, and the principle that Hong Kong and Macao SARs should be administered by patriots has been applied in these two regions, the report noted. "We have ensured that Hong Kong has entered a new stage in which it has restored order and is set to thrive," said the report. The central government has promoted the development of the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area and supported Hong Kong and Macao in developing their economies, improving living standards, responding to COVID-19 and maintaining stability, it said. The report added that efforts have also been made to resolutely fight separatism and interference and to further promote the peaceful development of cross-strait relations. (Cover: An aerial photo of the Hong Kong-Zhuhai-Macao Bridge. /Xinhua)